text: Rylan Wiens (born January 2, 2002) is a Canadian diver. He has competed in the 10 m synchro and 10 m platform events. Wiens first competed professionally for the Canadian national team at the 2018 Commonwealth Games where he finished 8th the platform and 6th in the synchro events. Before becoming an Olympian, Wiens won a bronze medal at the 2021 Diving World Cup, two silver medal at the 2022 Commonwealth Games, a silver medal at the 2022 World Aquatics Championships, and a silver medal at the 2023 Pan America Games. Wiens is a two-time Olympian. He competed at the 2020 Summer Olympics finishing in 19th place. Wiens, along with his diving partner Nathan Zsombor-Murray, competed for Canada in the 10 m synchro event at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France. The pair would end up winning bronze medals, making it the first time that a Canadian has medaled in the event at the Olympics. ==References== ==Other websites== *World Aquatics profile *Canadian Olympic team profile Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian divers Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Canada Category:Sportspeople from Calgary Category:Sportspeople from Saskatoon
